CatDescriptText: Ella Casson, Box 1007 Price Road, Presto, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 8, 1959, pg. B1 with question: "Do you believe the John James Racket Squad is driving the numbers racket out of Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "They are trying, but it will be a hard job to drive the numbers racket out of Pittsburgh. They certainly are making a good stab and this is good, because anything illegal which is done to excess tends to be done openly.  And this is bad."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Ella Casson wearing dark, nubby, short sleeved dress and necklace with teardrop stone or pearl, holding paper bag inscribed "Allens," standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Thrift Drugs and Kappels in background, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
